  <Summary>Revolt of the Fingers: Antonini Bellt, a brilliant young musician, has no control over his left hand he calls "Dividi". When his mentor Provak starts bullying him, Bellt's hand goes berserk.

The Black Candle of Life: Jeff and Marjorie Capper are traveling through Tibet when they have to seek shelter in a cave from a rainstorm. By lighting a black candle the tourists revive the zombie-like "evil ones".

The Crawling Horror: Titus Grimm and Wilbur Hatch are scientists who invented a living mass of protoplasm and an electronic brain. Grimm is willing to hook the brain to the blob and create "a creature far superior to man".

</Summary>
